                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Pearson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-02-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Pearson states, in reply to the telegram of the 12th, that the Shah, through
                    the Persian minister of foreign affairs, has given emphatic assurance that the
                    accomplices shall be punished before next January. After full conference with
                    Mr. Pearson, the British minister withdrew the British consul-general from
                    Urumia. They do not anticipate any disorder, but believe that the Kurds will not
                    be recaptured except by force.)</p>
            </div>
